OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1773846666
OL,3,CUnite the Union to pay #435,000 over
OL,4,C'illegal' Birmingham bin strike pickets
OL,6,FUnite the Union has to pay #435,000 in
OL,7,Ffines and costs after a High Court
OL,8,Fruling found they "illegally picketed"
OL,9,Fduring the Birmingham bin strikes.
OL,11,FThe judgement made on Tuesday, 17
OL,12,FMarch, found that Unite should be
OL,13,Ffined for breaching an injunction
OL,14,Frelating to strike action.
OL,16,FUnite has been ordered to pay #265,000
OL,17,Fin fines to the Government and also
OL,18,F#170,000 in costs to the claimant,
OL,19,FBirmingham City Council.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/15
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1773846666
OL,3,CUnite the Union to pay #435,000 over
OL,4,C'illegal' Birmingham bin strike pickets
OL,6,FBirmingham City Council sought the
OL,7,Finjunction to halt protests outside of
OL,8,Fits depots amid ongoing demonstrations
OL,9,Fin support of striking bin workers.
OL,11,FUpon receiving the fine, Unite has
OL,12,Fvowed that it will not allow
OL,13,FBirmingham bin workers "to pay the
OL,14,Fprice for the council's failings".
OL,16,FBirmingham City Council were pleased
OL,17,Fwith the outcome. It said: "We are
OL,18,Fworking to keep the city safe and
OL,19,Fclean.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/15
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1773846666
OL,3,CUnite the Union to pay #435,000 over
OL,4,C'illegal' Birmingham bin strike pickets
OL,6,F"This judgement confirms that Unite
OL,7,Fhas tried to prevent us from
OL,8,Fcollecting our residents' bins and to
OL,9,Ffill the city up with rubbish."
OL,11,FBin workers have been striking since
OL,12,FJanuary 2025 and members of Unite
OL,13,Fstarted a continuous walkout on March
OL,14,F11, last year in a dispute over pay,
OL,15,Fwith little sign of a breakthrough in
OL,16,Fthe deadlocked row.
OL,18,FThe union says planned reforms of the
OL,19,Frefuse collection service will lead to
OL,20,Fhundreds of its members losing
OL,21,Fthousands of pounds.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/15
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1773846666
OL,3,CUnite the Union to pay #435,000 over
OL,4,C'illegal' Birmingham bin strike pickets
OL,6,FHowever, the council denies the claim
OL,7,Fand is pressing ahead with changes it
OL,8,Fsays are needed to improve the service.
OL,10,FHigh Court ruling finds Unite
OL,11,F"deliberately" breached injunction
OL,13,FThe High Court Judge, Mrs Justice
OL,14,FJefford DBE, found that Unite
OL,15,Fdeliberately breached an injunction
OL,16,Fthat was issued on May 23, 2025.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/15
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1773846666
OL,3,CUnite the Union to pay #435,000 over
OL,4,C'illegal' Birmingham bin strike pickets
OL,6,FIt followed a number of protests
OL,7,Fearlier in 2025, which prevented the
OL,8,Fdeployment of any bin-collecting
OL,9,Fvehicles from any of Birmingham's
OL,10,Fthree depots, Atlas, Lifford Lane and
OL,11,FPerry Barr.
OL,13,FAs part of the injunction, there could
OL,14,Fbe no more than six pickets at any
OL,15,Fdepot entrance. Pickets were also
OL,16,Fordered to "refrain from seeking to
OL,17,Fprevent any vehicle from passing
OL,18,Fthrough the site entrance to each of
OL,19,Fthe Depots".
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/15
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1773846666
OL,3,CUnite the Union to pay #435,000 over
OL,4,C'illegal' Birmingham bin strike pickets
OL,6,FThe injunction was found to be
OL,7,Fbreached on every weekday between July
OL,8,F8, 2025 and July 21, 2025.
OL,10,FEvidence was also put forward to the
OL,11,FHigh Court from Birmingham City
OL,12,FCouncil that further breaches took
OL,13,Fplace between 22 and 30 July, 2025.
OL,14,FThe court says this was not challenged
OL,15,Fby Unite.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/15
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1773846666
OL,3,CUnite the Union to pay #435,000 over
OL,4,C'illegal' Birmingham bin strike pickets
OL,6,FDuring the hearing, Annmarie Kilcline,
OL,7,Fthe Unite Regional Secretary for the
OL,8,FWest Midlands, accepted Unite had
OL,9,Fbreached the court's order. However
OL,10,FUnite said it had thought that the
OL,11,Finjunction did not "prohibit
OL,12,Fprotesting a little way away" from the
OL,13,Fdepot.
OL,15,FMs Kilcline also said there had been
OL,16,Fno breaches since 31 July, 2025, and
OL,17,Fshe assured the court that Unite would
OL,18,Fcomply with the injunction going
OL,19,Fforward.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/15
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1773846666
OL,3,CUnite the Union to pay #435,000 over
OL,4,C'illegal' Birmingham bin strike pickets
OL,6,FHowever in the 21-page judgment, Mrs
OL,7,FJustice Jefford said: "I cannot accept
OL,8,Fthat when Unite offered an assurance
OL,9,Fthat protesting would be limited to
OL,10,Fthe assembly areas, anyone giving
OL,11,Finstructions for that assurance to be
OL,12,Foffered would have intended that the
OL,13,Fprotests could just be moved a few
OL,14,Fhundred metres away from the depots so
OL,15,Fthat the vehicles that had left the
OL,16,Fdepots could then be obstructed and
OL,17,Fdelayed at a different point in their
OL,18,Froute."
OL,26,@oD@WOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/15
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1773846666
OL,3,CUnite the Union to pay #435,000 over
OL,4,C'illegal' Birmingham bin strike pickets
OL,6,FUnite has denied there has been abuse
OL,7,Fand intimidation carried out during
OL,8,Fthe pickets.
OL,10,FUnite calls the ruling "another
OL,11,Fpathetic attempt to intimidate workers"
OL,13,FFollowing the High Court ruling, Unite
OL,14,Fgeneral secretary Sharon Graham said:
OL,15,F"This is yet another pathetic attempt
OL,16,Fto intimidate workers and it won't
OL,17,Fwork.
OL,19,F"Unite will not allow these workers to
OL,20,Fpay the price for the council's
OL,21,Ffailings in their pay packets.
OL,26,@wD@AOU{D@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G9/15
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37810
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1773846666
OL,3,CUnite the Union to pay #435,000 over
OL,4,C'illegal' Birmingham bin strike pickets
OL,6,F"Instead of using Thatcher's anti-
OL,7,Funion laws to 'injunct' the picket
OL,8,Fline and stop lawful protest, the
OL,9,Fcouncil should honour the deal scoped
OL,10,Fout at Acas.
OL,12,F"They walked out of the room, said
OL,13,Fthey would be back with the deal in
OL,14,Fwriting, and never returned.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G10/15
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37811
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1773846666
OL,3,CUnite the Union to pay #435,000 over
OL,4,C'illegal' Birmingham bin strike pickets
OL,6,F"Rather than resolving the dispute,
OL,7,FBirmingham City Council's own figures
OL,8,Fhave confirmed they have spent #33
OL,9,Fmillion pounds of Birmingham
OL,10,Fresidents' money trying to break the
OL,11,Fstrike. It won't be broken - these
OL,12,Fworkers are fighting for council
OL,13,Fworkers everywhere.
OL,15,F"Unite is very relaxed about the fine,
OL,16,Fevery single penny will come out of
OL,17,FLabour's affiliation fee."
OL,19,FBirmingham City Council insists "going
OL,20,Fto court was not something we wanted
OL,21,Fto do"
OL,26,@nD@AOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G11/15
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37812
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1773846666
OL,3,CUnite the Union to pay #435,000 over
OL,4,C'illegal' Birmingham bin strike pickets
OL,6,FCllr Majid Mahmood, Cabinet Member for
OL,7,FEnvironment and Transport, said: "We
OL,8,Fare pleased the judge has accepted the
OL,9,Fevidence that members of Unite the
OL,10,FUnion repeatedly breached the
OL,11,Finjunction ordered by the court last
OL,12,Fyear.
OL,14,F"We are working to keep the city safe
OL,15,Fand clean. This judgement confirms
OL,16,Fthat Unite has tried to prevent us
OL,17,Ffrom collecting our residents' bins
OL,18,Fand to fill the city up with rubbish.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G12/15
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37813
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1773846666
OL,3,CUnite the Union to pay #435,000 over
OL,4,C'illegal' Birmingham bin strike pickets
OL,6,F"The fine of #265,000 (plus #170,000
OL,7,Finterim payment in relation to
OL,8,FBirmingham City Council's legal costs)
OL,9,Fwas issued by the judge ` will send a
OL,10,Fclear message about what is acceptable
OL,11,Fbehaviour and what is not.
OL,13,F"Going to court was not something we
OL,14,Fwanted to do but were left with no
OL,15,Foption. We always acknowledged that
OL,16,Feveryone has the right to protest and
OL,17,Fthat Unite has the right to organise
OL,18,Fpicketing in line with their statutory
OL,19,Frights. However, people also have a
OL,20,Fright to work.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G13/15
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37814
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1773846666
OL,3,CUnite the Union to pay #435,000 over
OL,4,C'illegal' Birmingham bin strike pickets
OL,6,F"What is not acceptable is for pickets
OL,7,Fto obstruct vehicles and prevent
OL,8,Fpeople from doing so. This was
OL,9,Fconfirmed when the interim injunction
OL,10,Fwas issued and that injunction remains
OL,11,Fin place today.
OL,13,F"We will continue to use all legal
OL,14,Fmeans to protect our staff and
OL,15,Fresidents and maintain essential
OL,16,Fservices, in the face of determined
OL,17,Fattempts at disruption."
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G14/15
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
